which are so agreeable to our Reason, and do so plainly <lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <fw type="pageNum">B 3</fw>
                  <pb n="15"/> 
                  <lb/>
conduce to our own truest interest and advantage, both in <lb/>
this Life, and that to come, as will appear by what follows. <lb/>
(6.) Consider therefore in the next place, that it is a <lb/>
most certain truth, That the leading of an holy and good <lb/>
Life, is in all respects very greatly for a Man's own benefit <lb/>
and comfort, even in this present World. <quote type="biblical" ana="1 Tim 4.8">Godliness is profitable <lb/>
