along with it all manner of Blessings, and makes the enjoyment <lb/>
of them more sweet and pleasant, and keeps off <lb/>
a great deal of trouble which wicked men bring upon <lb/>
themselves, and affords much support and ease under <lb/>
those afflictions which the providence of God may lay <lb/>
upon us. <normalised orig="Insomuch" auto="true">Inasmuch</normalised> that no Man of what rank and condition <lb/>
<normalised orig="soever" auto="true">however</normalised>, can lead a truly comfortable Life, except <lb/>
he lead an holy and good life. All this is frequently <lb/>
